from: 15, her peeing and running off was when she first came to live with me.  She'd been kept in a pen.  I took her from those people when they moved away. Initially upon coming home with me, any time she had the chance to get out, off she'd go.  She did not know how to ask to go out then, either.  I taught her to come and to ring the bell and she's not been a problem for the rest of her life, except now she has old age anxiety which makes her pee when I'm not home.  I'm not sure about the questions on this test.  They don't seem to gather the entire situation.
